<TD align="left"><pre>

<strong>DISK I/O FUNCTIONS:</strong><br>
    There are two distinct ways to perform file operations in C .<br>
          1. Low-Level I/O and uses UNIX system calls .<br>
          2. High-Level I/O library.<br>
         High Level I/O functions are more commonly used in C programs, since they are easier to use
 than Low Level disk I/O functions . There is one difference between High Level and Low Level disk I/O 
 functions . High Level disk I/O functions do their own buffer management , where as in Low Level Disk I/O
 functions, buffer management has to be done explicitly by the programmer.
                       
